<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="25">1.2. Deleting categories in the ShopBuilder</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>You can delete categories in the content manager view. Please be aware that deleting a category also deletes the contents that are linked with this category.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Deleting a category:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>CMS » ShopBuilder</strong>.<br>
→ The content manager view of the ShopBuilder opens.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>In the category tree on the left, click on the <strong>edit</strong> symbol in the row of the category you want to delete.<br>
→ The <strong>Edit category</strong> window opens.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the <strong>delete</strong> button.<br>
→ The <strong>Delete category</strong> window opens.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Delete category</strong>.<br>
→ The category is deleted.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="26">1.3. Linking categories with the Ceres plugin</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>You need to link a few categories in a separate step with the Ceres plugin, so that these categories work properly in the online store. At the moment, you need to link the categories for the <strong>checkout</strong>, the <strong>My Account</strong> area, and the <strong>information about shipping costs</strong>. Proceed as follows to link the categories:</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Linking a category with Ceres:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>CMS » ShopBuilder</strong>.<br>
→ The content manager view of the ShopBuilder opens.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Open settings</strong> on the left in the toolbar.<br>
→ The interface for linking category opens.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click one of the rows, e.g. <strong>Category of “My Account”</strong>.<br>
→ The category selection opens.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select the category that you created for the corresponding section.<br>
→ The selected category is highlighted in blue.</p>
</li>
<li>
