<div class="title">Types of content</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>You select one of 3 types when you create a new content:
- Contents of the type <strong>Content</strong> are used for the homepage and additional static pages, such as a company history or your shipping cost information.</p>
</div>
<div class="ulist">
<ul>
<li>
<p>You select the type Checkout for setting up your order process.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Contents of the type <strong>My Account</strong> are used for the customer area of your online store.</p>
</li>
</ul>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Creating a content:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>CMS » ShopBuilder</strong>.<br>
→ The content manager view of the ShopBuilder opens.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select the category for which you want to create a content in the category tree on the left.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the <strong>new</strong> tile.<br>
→ The window <strong>Create new page</strong> opens.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select the content <strong>type</strong>.<br>
→ Select <strong>content</strong> for the homepage and static pages, <strong>checkout</strong> for your order process, or <strong>My Account</strong> for your customer area.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Enter a name for the content.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select a preset if necessary.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> the settings.<br>
→ The newly created page is displayed in the overview.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
